'''''If an Angel Came to See You, Would You Make Her Feel at Home?''''' is a [[studio album]] released by [[Southern rock]] band [[Black Oak Arkansas]] in 1972. It is the recording debut of drummer [[Tommy Aldridge]].

==Track listing==
All selections written by Black Oak Arkansas.
# "Gravel Roads" - 3:11
# "Fertile Woman" - 5:18
# "Spring Vacation" - 3:01  
# "We Help Each Other" - 3:12
# "Full Moon Ride" - 3:46 
# "Our Minds Eye" - 4:13 
# "To Make Us What We Are" - 4:53
# "Our Eyes Ere on You" - 3:45
# "Mutants of the Monster" - 4:44

==Personnel==
*Jim "Dandy" Mangrum: [[Lead Vocals]], [[Washboard (musical instrument)|Washboard]]
*Rickie "Ricochet" Reynolds: [[12 String Guitar|12 String Rhythm Guitar]], [[Vocal]]s
*Pat "Dirty" Daugherty: [[Bass Guitar]], [[Vocals]]
*Harvey "Burley" Jett: [[Lead Guitar]], [[Banjo]], [[Piano]], [[Vocal]]s
*Stanley "Goober" Knight: [[Lead Guitar|Lead]] & [[Steel Guitar]], [[Organ (music)|Organ]], [[Vocal]]s
*[[Tommy Aldridge|Tommy "T.A." Aldridge]]: [[Drums]]

==Production==
*Published by Far Fetched Music ([[ASCAP]]).
*Produced by [[Tom Dowd]].
*Executive Producers: Doc Siegel.
*Recorded at Paramamount Recording Studios and *Gold Star Recording Studios, Hollywood, Calif. 
*Engineers: [[The Albert Brothers|Howie Albert and Ron Albert]].
*Remixed by Tom Dowd and Doc Siegel.
*Cover design and photos by Les Weisbrich.
